    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\r\n\r\nPresent in at least 7c997dbc5db145ccfa3c4d687b85168819c8b7d2\r\n\r\n### Feature description\r\n\r\nLooking through the stylize_markdown function used by the hover -> open_floating_preview function:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7c997dbc5db145ccfa3c4d687b85168819c8b7d2/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua#L1185\r\n\r\nIt seems like the markdown parsing ignores markdown links. Would you be open to a PR for updating that parser to support them?\r\n\r\nAny ramifications or other systems that this could cause harm to?\r\n\r\nWithout the parsing, links are rendered like this:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/590297/190975546-7bc4c04a-05f1-43ba-81ed-003c144b8006.png)\r\n\r\nI think parsing them fully so they are interactive would be nice to have. Alternatively, just displaying one url if the url and display are the same without the markup would be sufficient.",
