        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "If implemented it would also be nice to have an option to conceal the URL part. Especially with Javadoc the lengthy `jdt:/` links are all over the place and make the text quite noisy and hard to read.\r\n\r\nSo far I've used a workaround that I found [here](https://github.com/mfussenegger/nvim-jdtls/discussions/124#discussioncomment-1968776):\r\n\r\n> You could add some conceal definitions. For example create a file `lsp_markdown.vim` within `.config/nvim/after/syntax/`:\r\n> \r\n> ```viml\r\n> syn clear markdownLink\r\n> syn region markdownLink matchgroup=markdownLinkDelimiter start=\"(\" end=\")\" contains=markdownUrl,mkJdtLink keepend contained\r\n> syntax match mkJdtLink /jdt:\\/\\/.*/ containedin=markdownLink conceal\r\n> ```\r\n> ",
